Description: Small clay bulla in a ball-shape, made of dark brown Nile clay that was consolidated after excavation leading to a darker colouration. On the surface parts of six shallow seal impressions of an oval scarab-like seal. The surface is quite uneven, roughly formed and finished. The motif of the seal is almost illegible, one impression shows a mn-sign at the top. It is not clear if all impressions originate from the same seal.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.20B, lower levels
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 111)
